The paper proposes a new deep learning model for multi-view learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks and optimization techniques, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image datasets, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a new loss function that can be applied to other deep models, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
